criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Totally impacted mandibular third molars of class C, 1, 2, and 3 according to the
             Pell-Gregory classification;

          -  Has no systemic disease

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  The use of medications that could interfere with the healing process;

          -  Smoking;

          -  Pregnancy or lactation;

          -  Presence of any condition, such as inflammation, periodontitis, gingivitis and dental
             abscess in the area of the impacted teeth;

          -  Undergoing antibiotic or anti-inflammatory drugs therapies in the 7 days before
             surgery;

          -  History of hypersensitivity to iodine;

          -  Has any thyroid diseases.
